article:
'Stars & Stripes' may refer to:
* a nickname for the Flag of the United States *''Stars & Stripes'' (album),
  2002 album by Aaron Tippin *''Stars & Stripes'' (yacht), a series of America's
  Cup competitors *Stars & Stripes (soft drink), a soft drink brand *''Stars and
  Stripes'' (ballet), choreographed by George Balanchine in 1958 *''Stars and
  Stripes'' (newspaper), official newspaper of the United States Armed Forces
  *[[Stars and Stripes trilogy]], a collection of three alternate history novels
  by Harry Harrison *[[Stars and Stripes Vol. 1]], 1996 album by The Beach Boys
  *Stars and Stripes (wrestling team), a World Championship Wrestling tag team
  *[[The Stars and Stripes Forever]], the national march of the United States
